President Obama has declared a major disaster in West Virginia due to severe winter storms, flooding, landslides, and mudslides that occurred from March 3-6, 2015. Federal aid will be provided to supplement state and local recovery efforts. The funding will be used for emergency work, repairing or replacing damaged facilities, and implementing hazard mitigation measures. The declaration covers multiple counties in West Virginia, and additional designations may be made based on further damage assessments. Kari Suzann Cowie has been named as the Federal Coordinating Officer for federal recovery operations in the affected area.